A (smooth) //section// of a vector bundle $$\pi\colon E\to M$$ is a (smooth) map $$\sigma\colon M\to E$$ such that $$\pi\circ\sigma=\id_M,$$ meaning $$\sigma(p)\in E_p$$ for each $$p\in M.$$

The space of all sections is denoted $$\Gamma(E).$$ It is always a module over $$\mathcal C^\infty(M).$$